> times the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apothem" title=3D"Apot=
hem">apothem</a><sup id=3D"cite_ref-Johnson_5-0" class=3D"reference"><a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Regular_polygon#cite_note-Johnson-5"><sp=
an class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a=
></sup><sup class=3D"reference nowrap"><span title=3D"Page / location: p. 7=
2">:=E2=80=8Ap. 72=E2=80=8A</span></sup> (the apothem being the distance fr=
om the center to any side). This is a generalization of <a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Viviani%27s_theorem" title=3D"Viviani's theorem">Vivi=
ani's theorem</a> for the <i>n</i> =3D 3 case.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-6" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Regular_polygon#cit=
e_note-6"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-7" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Regular_polygon#cite_note-7"><span class=3D"ci=
te-bracket">[</span>6<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
