egular polygons</a>)</span>.
</p><p>The sum of the perpendiculars from a regular <i>n</i>-gon's vertices=
 to any line tangent to the circumcircle equals <i>n</i> times the circumra=
dius.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Johnson_5-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Regular_polygon#cite_note-Johnson-5"><span class=3D=
"cite-bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup=
 class=3D"reference nowrap"><span title=3D"Page / location: p. 73">:=E2=80=
=8Ap. 73=E2=80=8A</span></sup>
</p><p>The sum of the squared distances from the vertices of a regular <i>n=
</i>-gon to any point on its circumcircle equals 2<i>nR</i><sup>2</sup> whe=
re <i>R</i> is the circumradius.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Johnson_5-2" class=3D"r=
eference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Regular_polygon#cite_not=
e-Johnson-5"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-brac=
ket">]</span></a></sup><sup class=3D"reference nowrap"><span title=3D"Page =
/ location: p. 73">:=E2=80=8Ap. 73=E2=80=8A</span></sup>
</p><p>The sum of the squared distances from the midpoints of the sides of =
a regular <i>n</i>-gon to any point on the circumcircle is 2<i>nR</i><sup>2=
</sup> =E2=88=92 <span class=3D"sfrac">=E2=81=A0<span class=3D"tion"><span =
class=3D"num">1</span><span class=3D"sr-only">/</span><span class=3D"den">4=
</span></span>=E2=81=A0</span><i>ns</i><sup>2</sup>, where <i>s</i> is the =
side length and <i>R</i> is the circumradius.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Johnson_5-=
3" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Regular_pol=
ygon#cite_note-Johnson-5"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup class=3D"reference nowrap"><span t=
itle=3D"Page / location: p. 73">:=E2=80=8Ap. 73=E2=80=8A</span></sup>
</p>
