<p>A non-convex regular polygon is a regular <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Star_polygon" title=3D"Star polygon">star polygon</a>. The most =
common example is the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pentagram" t=
itle=3D"Pentagram">pentagram</a>, which has the same vertices as a <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pentagon" title=3D"Pentagon">pentagon</a>=
, but connects alternating vertices.
</p><p>For an <i>n</i>-sided star polygon, the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Schl%C3%A4fli_symbol" title=3D"Schl=C3=A4fli symbol">Schl=C3=
=A4fli symbol</a> is modified to indicate the <i>density</i> or "starriness=
" <i>m</i> of the polygon, as {<i>n</i>/<i>m</i>}. If <i>m</i> is 2, for ex=
ample, then every second point is joined. If <i>m</i> is 3, then every thir=
d point is joined. The boundary of the polygon winds around the center <i>m=
</i> times.
</p><p>The (non-degenerate) regular stars of up to 12 sides are:
</p>
<ul><li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pentagram" title=3D"Pentag=
ram">Pentagram</a> =E2=80=93 {5/2}</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heptagram" title=3D"Heptagram"=
>Heptagram</a> =E2=80=93 {7/2} and {7/3}</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Octagram" title=3D"Octagram">O=
ctagram</a> =E2=80=93 {8/3}</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Enneagram_(geometry)" title=3D=
"Enneagram (geometry)">Enneagram</a> =E2=80=93 {9/2} and {9/4}</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Decagram_(geometry)" title=3D"=
Decagram (geometry)">Decagram</a> =E2=80=93 {10/3}</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hendecagram" title=3D"Hendecag=
ram">Hendecagram</a> =E2=80=93 {11/2}, {11/3}, {11/4} and {11/5}</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dodecagram" title=3D"Dodecagra=
m">Dodecagram</a> =E2=80=93 {12/5}</li></ul>
<p><i>m</i> and <i>n</i> must be <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C=
oprime" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Coprime">coprime</a>, or the figure =
will degenerate.
</p><p>The degenerate regular stars of up to 12 sides are:
</p>
<ul><li>Tetragon =E2=80=93 {4/2}</li>
<li>Hexagons =E2=80=93 {6/2}, {6/3}</li>
<li>Octagons =E2=80=93 {8/2}, {8/4}</li>
<li>Enneagon =E2=80=93 {9/3}</li>
<li>Decagons =E2=80=93 {10/2}, {10/4}, and {10/5}</li>
<li>Dodecagons =E2=80=93 {12/2}, {12/3}, {12/4}, and {12/6}</li></ul>
